1. Refugees and economic migrants are not the same thing.2. It's not fair to label all refugees as "economic migrants" or "invaders".3. Colonizing a country is not something that refugees can do.4. There are many reasons why people leave their home countries, and it's not always easy to distinguish between a refugee and an economic migrant.5. Countries have the right to set their own immigration policies, but it's important to remember that refugees are human beings who deserve compassion and protection.6. Stereotyping and stigmatizing entire groups of people based on their nationality or immigration status is not a solution to the complex issue of migration.Instead of spreading hate and fear, let's focus on finding ways to help refugees and other migrants integrate into their new communities and contribute to their new countries. Let's work together to create a more welcoming and inclusive world. #WelcomeRefugees #BuildBridgesNotWalls #DiversityIsStrength
